description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialist Detoxification Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post provides an exciting opportunity for the right candidate as it will deliver positive clinical work in supporting service users to become drug and alcohol free&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also be supported in undertaking their non-medical prescriber training to become a supplementary prescriber.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is part of wider multi-disciplinary team which includes a clinical psychologist, Associate specialist, non-medical prescribers, Nurses, Social Workers &amp; Recovery Workers supported by the clinical lead, a consultant addiction psychiatrist, who are employed by AWP within Specialist Drug &amp; Alcohol Service (SDAS) Bournemouth, Christchurch &amp; Poole (BCP). Hence the role is connected to and supported by NHS governance and expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have the pre-requisite skills and qualities that value the dividends that partnership working provides in a fluid, active and changing working environment that requires an organised, dynamic, compassionate and competent nurse who can support service users achieve their self-determined optimised outcomes then we are keen to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note, d&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ue to the nature of delivering community detoxes the days of work are required to be Monday to Thursday&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A driving licence is essential. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Daniel Willingale, BCP Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address  dan.willingale@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01202977010&lt;/p&gt;
